# Tools

Some simple tools for my own productivity.

---

## pass - Password Store Replacement

A Windows-compatible replacement for the Unix [password-store](https://www.passwordstore.org/) (`pass`) tool.

### Overview

`pass` manages GPG-encrypted password files in `~/.password-store/` with git integration for version control. This implementation provides the same basic functionality as the Unix version but is built in Go for cross-platform compatibility.

### Prerequisites

- **Go 1.20+** - For building the tool
- **GnuPG (GPG)** - For encryption/decryption (GPG4Win on Windows)
- **Git** - For version control integration

### Installation

#### 1. Install Dependencies

**Windows:**
- Install [Go](https://golang.org/dl/) (1.20 or later)
- Install [GPG4Win](https://www.gpg4win.org/)
- Install [Git for Windows](https://gitforwindows.org/)

**Linux/macOS:**
```bash
# Debian/Ubuntu
sudo apt install golang gnupg git

# RHEL/CentOS
sudo dnf install golang gnupg git

# macOS (Homebrew)
brew install go gnupg git
```

#### 2. Build from Source

```bash
# Clone the repository (if not already cloned)
git clone <repository-url>
cd tools

# Build the pass binary
cd pass
go build -o pass.exe .

# On Linux/macOS:
go build -o pass .
```

#### 3. Install the Binary

**Windows:**
```cmd
copy pass\pass.exe C:\Windows\System32\
```

**Linux/macOS:**
```bash
sudo cp pass/pass /usr/local/bin/
```

Or add the `pass/` directory to your PATH.

### Usage

#### Basic Commands

```bash
# List all passwords
pass ls

# List passwords under a specific path
pass ls email/

# Show a password
pass email/gmail.com/myemail@gmail.com

# Copy password to clipboard
pass -c email/gmail.com/myemail@gmail.com

# Insert a new password
pass insert email/gmail.com/myemail@gmail.com

# Search for passwords
pass find gmail

# Show help
pass --help
pass insert --help
```

#### Configuration

Set environment variables to customize behavior:

```bash
# Custom password store location
export PASSWORD_STORE_DIR="$HOME/custom/passwords"

# Specific GPG key ID
export PASS_GPG_ID="ABCD1234"

# Clipboard auto-clear timeout (seconds)
export PASS_CLIPBOARD_TIMEOUT=60

# Disable clipboard auto-clear
export PASS_CLIPBOARD_CLEAR=false

# Git user override
export PASS_GIT_NAME="Your Name"
export PASS_GIT_EMAIL="your@email.com"
```

### Running Tests

#### Unit Tests

```bash
# Run all tests
cd pass
go test ./...

# Run tests with verbose output
go test -v ./...

# Run specific test package
go test -v ./pkg/gpg/

# Run specific test
go test -v -run TestShowCommand ./tests/
```

#### Manual Testing

```bash
# Build the binary
cd pass
go build -o pass.exe .

# Test listing (should show existing passwords if any)
./pass.exe ls

# Test finding
./pass.exe find gmail

# Test showing a password (will fail without proper GPG key)
./pass.exe email/gmail.com/myemail@gmail.com

# Test inserting a password
./pass.exe insert test/example
# Enter password twice when prompted
# Check that test/example.gpg was created

# Verify git integration
cd ~/.password-store
git log --oneline
```

### Project Structure

```
pass/
├── go.mod                    # Go module definition
├── main.go                   # Entry point
├── pass.exe                  # Compiled binary (Windows)
├── cmd/
│   ├── root.go               # Root command and global flags
│   ├── insert.go             # Insert command
│   ├── show.go               # Show command
│   ├── ls.go                 # List command
│   └── find.go               # Find command
├── pkg/
│   ├── gpg/                  # GPG encryption/decryption
│   │   └── gpg.go
│   ├── git/                  # Git integration
│   │   └── git.go
│   ├── filesystem/           # Filesystem utilities
│   │   └── fs.go
│   ├── clipboard/            # Clipboard operations
│   │   └── clipboard.go
│   └── config/               # Configuration
│       └── config.go
└── tests/
    └── show_test.go           # Test files
```

### Development

#### Adding New Commands

1. Create a new file in `cmd/` (e.g., `rm.go`)
2. Implement the command using cobra
3. Register it in `root.go` with `add<Command>Cmd()`
4. Add to `Execute()` function

Example structure:
```go
package cmd

var myCmd = &cobra.Command{
    Use:   "mycommand [args]",
    Short: "Description",
    RunE: func(cmd *cobra.Command, args []string) error {
        // Implementation
        return nil
    },
}

func addMyCmd() {
    rootCmd.AddCommand(myCmd)
}
```

#### Building for Different Platforms

```bash
# Windows
GOOS=windows GOARCH=amd64 go build -o pass-windows.exe .

# Linux
GOOS=linux GOARCH=amd64 go build -o pass-linux .

# macOS
GOOS=darwin GOARCH=amd64 go build -o pass-macos .

# ARM64
GOOS=windows GOARCH=arm64 go build -o pass-arm64.exe .
```

### Troubleshooting

**"gpg: command not found"**
- Ensure GPG is installed and in your PATH
- Windows: Check that `C:\Program Files (x86)\GnuPG\bin` is in PATH

**"No secret key available"**
- Generate a GPG key pair: `gpg --full-generate-key`
- Or import an existing key

**"git: command not found"**
- Ensure Git is installed and in your PATH
- Git integration is optional for basic operations

**"pass: command not found"**
- Ensure `pass.exe` or `pass` is in your PATH
- Or use the full path to the binary

